OL,3,CEpilepsy sufferer says welfare cuts an
OL,4,C'attack' on disabled people
OL,6,FWork and Pensions Secretary Liz
OL,7,FKendall outlined radical changes to
OL,8,Fthe benefits system in the House of
OL,9,FCommons on Tuesday in a bid to get
OL,10,Fmore people into work and save #5
OL,11,Fbillion by 2030.
OL,13,FThe changes include scrapping a
OL,14,Fcontroversial benefits assessment and
OL,15,Ftightening the eligibility criteria
OL,16,Ffor disability benefits.
OL,18,FMurray says the allowances help people
OL,19,Fwith disabilities "get on with their
OL,20,Fday to day life", and cuts will only
OL,21,Fmake their jobs and daily life harder.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/13
