OL,3,CEpilepsy sufferer says welfare cuts an
OL,4,C'attack' on disabled people
OL,6,FMurray says he has around five to six
OL,7,Fseizures a month which often take the
OL,8,Fform of absences, meaning he can walk
OL,9,Fwithout knowing what he's doing or
OL,10,Fwhere he's going for up to two minutes.
OL,12,FAs a result, he says he has almost
OL,13,Fwalked off a train platform three
OL,14,Ftimes while going to work.
OL,16,F"It is scary. It's the unknown. Every
OL,17,Fday is a risk to me," he told ITV News.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/13
