OL,3,CEpilepsy sufferer says welfare cuts an
OL,4,C'attack' on disabled people
OL,6,FMurray says it is already "extremely
OL,7,Fdifficult" to get Pip, adding that
OL,8,Fhe's had it taken away from him twice,
OL,9,Fbut each time he's managed to have the
OL,10,Fdecision overturned.
OL,12,FMurray says he feels "nervous" about
OL,13,Fthe changes announced by the
OL,14,Fgovernment, and that rather than
OL,15,Fhaving one system to "judge everyone",
OL,16,Fhe believes there should be different
OL,17,Fpathways for different conditions.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/13
