OL,3,CEpilepsy sufferer says welfare cuts an
OL,4,C'attack' on disabled people
OL,6,F"But what they're doing at the moment
OL,7,Fis they put all of those into one line
OL,8,Fand we all get judged the same way -
OL,9,Fand it's mainly physical."
OL,11,FHe continued: "I think they're going
OL,12,Fto make more loopholes than what
OL,13,Fthey've already got."
OL,15,FThe government says the cuts are part
OL,16,Fof efforts to find savings after
OL,17,Fglobal factors and slow economic
OL,18,Fgrowth tightened the Chancellor's
OL,19,Fspending flexibility.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/13
